.TH AI-PLAYBOOK 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook \- capture, author, and run terminal playbooks
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
ai\-playbook captures, authors, and runs terminal playbooks. Each
command below has its own manual page; run 'ai\-playbook <command>
\-\-help' or see ai\-playbook\-<command>(1) for full details.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBassist\fR
AI producer: capture context, triage, and author or drive a playbook
.TP
\fBcreate\fR
Author a playbook directly from a prompt (no triage, no cache serve)
.TP
\fBlist\fR
List every saved playbook
.TP
\fBsearch\fR
Search saved playbooks by substring
.TP
\fBshow\fR
Render a saved playbook read\-only
.TP
\fBedit\fR
Open a saved playbook in $EDITOR
.TP
\fBkb\fR
Browse, search, and edit the two\-set knowledge base
.TP
\fBskill\fR
Print or install the playbook\-authoring skill
.TP
\fBrun\fR
Run a playbook (interactive, headless, or guided)
.TP
\fBvalidate\fR
Check a playbook's structure and (optionally) get an AI review
.TP
\fBenv\fR
Print a playbook's declared env vars, resolved and redacted
.TP
\fBfinalize\fR
Backfill front matter onto an existing playbook file (manual)
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\-assist\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-create\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-list\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-search\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-show\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-edit\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-kb\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-skill\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-run\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-validate\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-env\fR(1), \fBai\-playbook\-finalize\fR(1)
